<!--946-->Evil Afoot x2<br />
Sarumans Ambition x3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok...truth be told I never have played this deck.  But I am sure some of you have.  I want to know how you think this would hold up?  I know Uruks are expensive.  But I happen to know that Elves and Men can move quickly and with the proper support stay alive.<br />
<br />
The only thing I can say - Sam, PP and Hobbit stealth are a good combo - And you can&#39;t go wrong with Arwen, ER - she can clean up your hand.<br />
(By the way - You can switch up Legolas, SoT and Arwen, ER for Aragorn, HttWC (just replace the KiE for another HttWC)).  No matter who you are you can&#39;t doctor anything to get a great hand.  <br />
Basically I am trying to set up a Fellowship to play any minions or any combo of minions.  This should be very effect.<br />
<br />
Minions are expensive - so what.  Play them anyway.  What about the Bridge?  You can always have fun at the Bridge, RUN you fools.  You don&#39;t run far with Uruks.  I figured Saruman can come in handy aroudn site 4, too.  Bluff your opponent - or don&#39;t - either way, someone gets hurt.  Captain is stictly for Lurtz and Saruman.  Don&#39;t get all crazy and pull out some half crappy Uruk.  <br />
<br />
Bid - Low or 0, let them play to your site - yes my sites suck, but thats the whole point.  Get you opponent thinking defesively make him/her play your game not theirs.  <br />
<br />
Well anyway - you anyone has questions d-mail me.<br />
<br />
